I"<h3 id="문제">문제</h3>

<p>Write a function <code class="highlighter-rouge">f(a, b)</code> which takes two strings as arguments and returns a string containing the characters found in both strings (without duplication), in the order that they appeared in <code class="highlighter-rouge">a</code>. Remember to skip spaces and characters you have already encountered!</p>

<p>Example: commonCharacters(‘acexivou’, ‘aegihobu’)
Returns: ‘aeiou’</p>

<p>Extra credit: Extend your function to handle more than two input strings.</p>

